@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Mental Health & Writing Journey";
}

<div class="content blog-content">
    <h1 class="text-center mb-4"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Mental Health & Writing Journey</span></h1>
    <img src="~/images/mental-health.png" alt="Mental Health and Writing" class="img-fluid rounded mx-auto d-block mb-4" style="max-height: 400px;" />

    <div class="content">
        <p>
            Writing can be both therapeutic and overwhelming. For many, blogging is more than just content—it's a form of self-expression, healing, and personal growth.
        </p>

        <h4>The Healing Power of Words</h4>
        <p>
            Sharing your story helps you release stress, validate your feelings, and connect with others going through similar experiences. It gives your pain a voice and transforms it into something meaningful.
        </p>

        <h4>Protecting Your Mental Space</h4>
        <p>
            While writing helps, it's essential to set boundaries. Don’t force content during burnout. Take breaks, and let your creative process be kind to your mind.
        </p>

        <h4>Finding Your Safe Audience</h4>
        <p>
            Communities like BlogVerse allow you to write freely without judgment. Whether anonymous or under your name, you're in charge of your narrative.
        </p>

        <p>
            Remember, your blog doesn’t need to be perfect—it just needs to be yours.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<script>
    setTimeout(() => {
        if (!sessionStorage.getItem('registerPromptShown')) {
            const shouldRedirect = confirm("Love writing? Join BlogVerse and share your journey. Want to register?");
            if (shouldRedirect) {
                window.location.href = "/Account/Register";
            }
            sessionStorage.setItem('registerPromptShown', 'true');
        }
    }, 3000);
</script>
